properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 19 at 5:57AM MST until February 20 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Goodland KS
properties.description:
...Light to moderate snowfall expected the Tri-State area this
afternoon into tonight...

* WHAT...2 to 4 inches of snow. A period of freezing drizzle
cannot be ruled out early this afternoon, prior to the onset of
snow. Breezy northeast winds ranging from 20 to 30 mph may
result in blowing snow this evening into tonight.

* WHERE...South of Interstate 70.

* WHEN...From 11 AM MST /noon CST/ Wednesday to 5 AM MST /6 AM
CST/ Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous travel conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel across the Advisory area this afternoon into
tonight, slow down, turn off cruise control, and exercise
additional caution, particularly at intersections and highway
onramps and offramps where accidents are more likely to occur.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM MST /NOON CST/ THIS MORNING TO 5 AM MST /6 AM CST/ THURSDAY
